    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a governing legislative body called a Senate, in ancient Rome and other states in antiquity, in some cities of Europe from Medieval to modern times, and in some modern nations such as the United States, Canada, France, and Italy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
